{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2017-10-09-drone-charger-v1/","webpackCompilationHash":"9b041b35cd2b91cc42b4","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Ten's Thoughts","author":"Ten Zhi Yang"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"908d4a91-e48d-5aea-9015-5ba40531cab8","excerpt":"Another quick but more useful project, I used what I learnt from the bench top power supply to make this USB power-cutter (for lack of a better name). I neededâ€¦","html":"<p>Another quick but more useful project, I used what I learnt from the bench top power supply to make this USB power-cutter (for lack of a better name). I needed a Device to turn off power after charging my Hubsan X4 for exactly 1 hour, as over charging the batteries was highly discouraged. I got a cheap Arduino micro clone I had lying around and attached it to a couple of female jumper wires. This was then connected to a relay. The timer is hardcoded into the Arduino. Maybe one day I will upgrade it with an LCD and some buttons, maybe use a one channel relay since that is all I need and put it in a proper enclosure. In the meantime, this will do!</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8298575e0b879741c17850d516abac1b/d6728/lipo.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.22263914946842%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"lipo\"\n        title=\"lipo\"\n        src=\"/static/8298575e0b879741c17850d516abac1b/c739e/lipo.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8298575e0b879741c17850d516abac1b